00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,830
It was in the early spring of 89, when the soot of London lay like a thin veil upon the day,

00:00:04,830 --> 00:00:08,300
that I first heard Holmes speak of the jewel they call the cat's eye,

00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:13,160
a green stone with a living fire that seemed to shift whenever the light touched it.

00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:16,259
Holmes and I sat in our familiar rooms at Baker Street,

00:00:16,259 --> 00:00:21,560
the cold rate breathing warmth, while outside the hansoms rattled and the wenders called,

00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:25,519
and within, quote, the violin keys lay open, as if it do listen for trouble.

00:00:25,519 --> 00:00:31,880
You are watching the street, Watson, but you are not observing it in any useful fashion,

00:00:31,880 --> 00:00:38,510
for your mind is still upon your hospital accounts and yesterday's dull argument with Stamford.

00:00:38,510 --> 00:00:42,519
I confess I started, for I had not spoken Stamford's name aloud,

00:00:42,519 --> 00:00:46,310
yet Holmes looked up from his chemical apparatus with that airy certainty,

00:00:46,310 --> 00:00:49,409
which always made my own thoughts feel loudly booted.

00:00:49,409 --> 00:00:52,939
The table before him held a shallow dish of crystals in a spirit lab,

00:00:52,939 --> 00:00:56,329
and a faint, sharp tang of reagents threaded the room,

00:00:56,329 --> 00:00:59,020
mixing oddly with the comforting scent of tea

00:00:59,020 --> 00:01:01,879
that Mrs. Dess' Hudson had recently brought.

00:01:01,879 --> 00:01:05,319
I had been at the window, idly noting passers-by

00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:08,359
and had not suspected that Holmes had once more

00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:10,760
been reading the invisible page of my expression

00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:12,760
with his detestable ease.

00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,700
Yet it was not long before events drew my attention

00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:17,090
from my own embarrassment,

00:01:17,090 --> 00:01:19,700
for the bell below rang with uncommon urgency

00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:22,879
and Mrs. Hudson's steps hurried upon the stair.

00:01:22,879 --> 00:01:28,140
Mr. H. Holmes sir, there is a lady below with a veil, and she says the matter is most immediate,

00:01:28,140 --> 00:01:32,139
and she will not be put off, not for kings, nor doctors, nor the whole of Scotton Yard.

00:01:32,139 --> 00:01:37,229
Show her up, Mrs. Hudson, and if she carries lavender upon her gloves,

00:01:37,229 --> 00:01:40,799
do ask her not to wave them about my experiments.

00:01:40,799 --> 00:01:42,120
..

00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:48,430
Mrs. H. Hudson gave me that long-suffering look which a mother grants to a gifted and impossible child,

00:01:48,430 --> 00:01:51,079
and withdrew, returning in moments with our visitor.

00:01:51,079 --> 00:01:58,079
her. Mr. Sherlock Holmes, I have come because the name of my family is at stake, and because a thing

00:01:58,079 --> 00:02:03,260
of great value has vanished under my roof, as if it had grown wings and flown through locked doors.

00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:07,870
She was tall and finely made, and though her face was half hidden by a dark veil,

00:02:07,870 --> 00:02:11,980
could see a proud line of chin, and the whiteness of her hand upon the rail.

00:02:11,980 --> 00:02:16,539
Her gown was rich yet restrained, the sort of elegance that disdains shouting,

00:02:16,539 --> 00:02:21,339
and there clung to her the faint perfume of violet and something sharper perhaps anxiety,

00:02:21,339 --> 00:02:22,810
which has its own odour.

00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:27,420
Pray be seated, madam, and if you will permit it, remove the veil,

00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:33,379
for it is tiresome to speak to a mystery while another mystery sits in front of it.

00:02:33,379 --> 00:02:36,199
You are direct to the point, Miss dear.

00:02:36,199 --> 00:02:39,590
Holmes, and so I shall endeavour to be the same,

00:02:39,590 --> 00:02:45,080
though my hands tremble and I do not thank you for noticing it before I have confessed as much.

00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:52,319
She lifted the veil and I saw a woman in her late twenties with grey eyes that held her steady courage in spite of their fatigue.

00:02:52,319 --> 00:03:07,810
I am Lady Adelaide Winterbourne of Winterbourne House in Kensington and last evening, during a small gathering of respectable friends, my husband's heirloom, the cat's eye, was stolen from the cabinet where it has lain for three generations.

00:03:07,810 --> 00:03:12,490
The cat's eye, yes, the stone the papers whisper of,

00:03:12,490 --> 00:03:16,030
and which the jewellers of Hatton Garden describe in reverent tones,

00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:22,269
as if it were a saint's relic rather than a bauble cut by human hands.

00:03:22,269 --> 00:03:26,110
I do not care what the papers whisper, Mr. Holmes,

00:03:26,110 --> 00:03:28,939
but I care very much what my husband will believe,

00:03:28,939 --> 00:03:33,050
for the cabinet was locked and the key was in my own possession.

00:03:33,050 --> 00:03:36,039
Holmes leaned back, steepling his long fingers,

00:03:36,039 --> 00:03:39,020
his eyes half-lidded in that curious posture

00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:41,439
which I had come to recognize as intense attention

00:03:41,439 --> 00:03:43,610
wearing the mask of languor.

00:03:43,610 --> 00:03:46,310
You held the key all evening,

00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:48,430
yet the jewel is gone.

00:03:48,430 --> 00:03:52,460
It suggests either that your key is not singular

00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:56,020
or that the cabinet did not require a key at all

00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:58,120
for the person who opened it.

00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:00,939
There is no second key, Mr. Yu.

00:04:00,939 --> 00:04:03,379
Holmes and the cabinet is a French piece

00:04:03,379 --> 00:04:04,319
with a trick mechanism

00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:08,829
which I alone was shown when my husband placed the jewel in my care.

00:04:08,829 --> 00:04:12,780
Then we shall begin, as ever, with the simplest facts.

00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:17,379
For everything is elementary until sentiment muddies the water.

00:04:17,379 --> 00:04:23,980
And sentiment, madam, is always the first refuge of those who dislike the truth.

00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:25,000
..

00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:29,120
Lady Winterbourne stiffened at that, but she did not retreat, which impressed me.

00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:33,399
For many clients recoil when Holmes treats their distress as an inconvenience.

00:04:33,399 --> 00:04:40,100
If you mean that you will accuse me, Mr. Ryday, Holmes, then do so plainly and be done,

00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:44,829
for I have come here to be saved from suspicion, not to be taught the manners of a laboratory.

00:04:44,829 --> 00:04:52,460
I mean that I will accuse no one until the evidence demands it. But I will question you,

00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:59,509
as if you were guilty, because only then will the innocent facts stand up and announce themselves.

00:04:59,509 --> 00:05:04,839
I could not help admiring that method, harsh as it sounded, for Holmes had taught me more

00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:07,889
than once that politeness is a poor lantern in dark corridors.

00:05:07,889 --> 00:05:13,939
Tell me of the cabinet, of the room, of the guests, and do not omit what you consider

00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:20,279
trivial, for the world is mostly made of trivialities arranged into a trap.

00:05:20,279 --> 00:05:26,620
The cabinet stands in my husband's study, a room that overlooks the garden, with two

00:05:26,620 --> 00:05:30,300
two tall windows and a single door opening into the gallery.

00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:34,350
Last evening we entertained only eight besides ourselves,

00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:37,899
Sir Lionel Greaves, Mrs. Greaves, Mr. Greaves,

00:05:37,899 --> 00:05:41,269
Mr. Percival Shaw, the art dealer,

00:05:41,269 --> 00:05:44,250
Miss Helena Shaw, his sister Colonel Rookwood,

00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:48,750
Reverend Giles Merriweather and my maid Elsie who served the tea.

00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:50,949
Holmes' eyes flickered, quick as a bird's,

00:05:50,949 --> 00:05:53,420
when she named the maid and I made a mental note,

00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:57,000
telling myself that I too would learn to value such small things.

00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:01,210
The maid served tea, yet you count her among the guests,

00:06:01,210 --> 00:06:04,639
which implies she moved freely and unremarked,

00:06:04,639 --> 00:06:09,180
the most dangerous condition for any person in any house.

00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:10,360
..

00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:14,540
Elsie has been with me two years and is as honest as any girl can be

00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:18,189
who has only her wages to hold, her upright in this city.

00:06:18,189 --> 00:06:23,279
Your faith is touching, but we are not discussing your heart, madam.

00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:31,199
We are discussing your jewel, and jewels, I have observed, tend to loosen the morals of saints.

00:06:31,199 --> 00:06:42,439
Lady Winterbourne coloured, yet forced herself to continue, and I could hear, us, beneath her composure, the fear of scandal, a dread far keener in her world than any dread of thieves.

00:06:42,439 --> 00:06:51,060
At nine o'clock we gathered in the drawing-room, and the study-door remained open, for my husband wished to displace certain prints he has acquired.

00:06:51,060 --> 00:07:00,370
The cabinet was closed and the cat's eye lay within its velvet niche, for earlier in the day I checked it myself, as I always do when we have visitors.

00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:13,980
You checked it earlier, which suggests you anticipated danger, which suggests you have had a warning, which suggests someone has been speaking of it beyond the walls of your house.

00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:21,060
I received a letter two days ago, Mr. Holmes, with no signature saying only,

00:07:21,060 --> 00:07:26,300
the cat's eye will blink for me and I burned it because I believed it a cruel jest.

00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:34,600
Shants, Holmes nodded once, as if the anonymous line had meetly snapped into a larger picture that only he could see.

00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:42,319
The phrase is theatrical, Watson, and the hand that writes theatrically often lives theatrically,

00:07:42,319 --> 00:07:47,220
which means we shall not confine ourselves to drawing rooms.

00:07:47,220 --> 00:07:52,540
I felt a thrill at that for any mention of movement beyond Baker Street promised action

00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:56,480
and action, I confess, is the tonic of my nature.

00:07:56,480 --> 00:08:02,079
Continue, Lady Winterbourne, and tell me precisely when you discovered the loss

00:08:02,079 --> 00:08:06,620
and precisely who had the opportunity to be alone with the cabinet.

00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:12,269
minute. At half past ten, my husband and Sir Lionel went to the study to view the newest print,

00:08:12,269 --> 00:08:18,620
and I followed some minutes later, for I heard my husband call my name. The men were standing

00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:24,480
near the desk, but the cabinet door stood ajar, and the velvet niche was empty, and I knew at

00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:29,439
once that the cat's eye was gone. She clasped her hands tightly then, and though her voice remained

00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:36,340
steady, her knuckles whitened as if she strutted not to break. And what did you do, madam, in that

00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:40,620
that first hot moment when foolish people ruin evidence with tears

00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:45,629
and wise people freeze the room as if it were a crime scene?

00:08:45,629 --> 00:08:49,470
I confess I did not freeze it, Mr. Cooler.

00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:52,340
Holmes, for I cried out and everyone came running

00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:56,379
and in an instant the study was full of voices and footsteps and the smell of panic.

00:08:56,379 --> 00:08:57,580
..

00:08:57,580 --> 00:09:01,500
Excellent. Then we shall have to work harder, which will amuse me.

00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,820
and we shall begin by visiting your house

00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:09,039
before memory becomes more imaginative than fact.

00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:11,039
Lady Winterbourne leaned forward.

00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:13,059
Hope and terror mingled in her gaze

00:09:13,059 --> 00:09:16,120
as if Holmes were both surgeon and judge.

00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:19,990
You will come at once, Mr. Into the Daylight Despair.

00:09:19,990 --> 00:09:23,360
Holmes, because my husband has already sent for the police

00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,419
and I dread what they will say

00:09:25,419 --> 00:09:27,519
and what the morning papers will do with it.

00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:28,559
..

00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:29,820
I will come at once, madam,

00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:36,379
madam, but understand me clearly. Scotland Yard will suspect the obvious, and the obvious is

00:09:36,379 --> 00:09:44,360
often wrong, yet it is wrong in a manner that destroys reputations. Therefore, if you wish my

00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:50,419
help, you will blunt me authority in your house for the next few hours, and you will permit me

00:09:50,419 --> 00:09:58,039
to question your guests and servants without interference. I will grant anything you ask,

00:09:58,039 --> 00:10:08,259
Mr. Bold, Mr. Holmes, if only you return the cat's eye and keep my family from becoming the jest of every club in Pormall. Mal!

00:10:08,259 --> 00:10:10,560
...

00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:21,559
Within minutes we were in our courts. Holmes with his long grey scarf and his curious mixture of haste and calm and I with that loyal readiness which, though it has led me into danger, I have never regretted.

00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:31,599
Bring your notebook, Watson, and do try, for once, to describe what you see rather than what you think you ought to have seen.

00:10:31,599 --> 00:10:37,759
His rebuke, gently delivered, struck true, and I resolved that this time I would be an observer,

00:10:37,759 --> 00:10:41,970
who'd not nearly a chronicler who arrives after Holmes has already harvested the field.

00:10:41,970 --> 00:10:46,740
A handsome carried us through the grimy arteries of London to Kensington,

00:10:46,740 --> 00:10:51,649
where Winterbourne House rose behind iron railings like a dignified prisoner.

00:10:51,649 --> 00:10:55,759
As we were shown into the gallery, I saw at once that the household was in turmoil,

00:10:55,759 --> 00:10:58,889
servants whispering in corners, and in the study beyond,

00:10:58,889 --> 00:11:02,819
the bulky figure of a policeman in blue stood like an accusation.

00:11:02,819 --> 00:11:06,890
Mr. Hum, Sherlock Holmes, I presume, and I'll tell you plain, sir,

00:11:06,890 --> 00:11:10,279
we've got a straightforward matter of a missing jewel and too many fingers in the room,

00:11:10,279 --> 00:11:12,580
which usually means the nearest hand took it.

00:11:12,580 --> 00:11:20,190
Inspector, your mind is like a shovel, useful for moving earth but disastrous for delicate work.

00:11:20,190 --> 00:11:24,740
So kindly stand aside while I look at what you have trampled.

00:11:24,740 --> 00:11:29,889
The inspector bristled, but Lady Winterbourne's anxious nod gave Holmes precedence,

00:11:29,889 --> 00:11:35,750
and my companion stepped into the study with the silent certainty of a man entering his natural habitat.

00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:42,379
Watson, note the scent in the air, note the ash on the rug, and note, above all,

00:11:42,379 --> 00:11:46,600
that the cabinet is open not by force but by familiarity.

00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,799
..

00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:51,769
I bent as Holmes bent, and as I inhaled I caught,

00:11:51,769 --> 00:11:55,340
beneath smoke and furniture polish, a faint anemone musk,

00:11:55,340 --> 00:11:58,019
as though some creature had recently been held close.

00:11:58,019 --> 00:11:59,040
..

00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:01,200
The cabinet, a bossy piece with gilded trim,

00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,180
showed no scratches near its lock,

00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:07,179
yet the velvet inside bore a slight indentation where the jewel had lain.

00:12:07,179 --> 00:12:08,259
..

00:12:08,259 --> 00:12:10,460
Observe that indentation, Watson,

00:12:10,460 --> 00:12:16,559
and observe the minute-green fleck at its edge, for even a jewel leaves a signature

00:12:16,559 --> 00:12:22,129
when removed in haste. I stared where he pointed, and indeed there was a speck,

00:12:22,129 --> 00:12:25,769
scarcely more than dust, which glimmered when the lamplight struck it.

00:12:25,769 --> 00:12:34,059
Now the question becomes not merely who wanted the cat's eye, but who had the composure to take it

00:12:34,059 --> 00:12:37,710
while a house full of people chattered within a few yards.

00:12:37,710 --> 00:12:42,940
Lady Winterbourne, take me to your maid and inspector if you wish to be useful.

00:12:42,940 --> 00:12:47,980
Prevent anyone from leaving the premises until I say otherwise.

00:12:47,980 --> 00:12:49,000
..

00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:54,080
The inspector muttered, yet complied and Lady Winterbourne led us toward the servant's corridor

00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:57,059
while I felt the case tighten like a noose.

00:12:57,059 --> 00:13:00,500
Holmes' stride was unhurried but his eyes moved constantly,

00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:05,299
counting door frames, reading scuffs, and collecting the silent testimony of the house.

00:13:05,299 --> 00:13:09,509
Watson, you see the scratch marks low upon this pantry door,

00:13:09,509 --> 00:13:13,370
and you think careless broom, but I think claws,

00:13:13,370 --> 00:13:18,550
and claws suggest a cat, and a cat suggests a purpose.

00:13:18,550 --> 00:13:22,179
Before I could frame a reply that met his standard of thirty characters

00:13:22,179 --> 00:13:25,860
and did not embarrass me, a thin cry sounded from within the kitchen,

00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,620
half gasp and half sob.

00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:35,910
mob. My lady, I swear by my mother's grave I never touched your jewel, and if anyone says I did,

00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:41,360
they are lying wickedly, because I would sooner cut off my own hands than bring ruin upon this

00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:46,860
house. Holmes lifted a finger for silence, and in that instant, as the maid's frightened eyes

00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:51,559
darted to the corner, I saw a wicker basket shift as though something living stirred within.

00:13:51,559 --> 00:13:55,940
There is your cat, Watson, and I would wager my violin.

00:13:55,940 --> 00:14:01,099
It has more to say about the cat's eye than any of these respectable mouths.

00:14:01,099 --> 00:14:05,690
Holmes stepped toward the basket, and as he did, a sleek black cat sprang out,

00:14:05,690 --> 00:14:12,200
its gaze bright and unsettling, and around its neck, to my astonishment, hung a torn scrap of green velvet.

00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:17,840
Elementary, Watson, that the jewel has travelled by a path no one thought to watch.

00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:23,340
watch, and now we shall learn who taught the cat to be a thief."

00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:28,980
In the cat's unblinking stare I felt the first true chill of the adventure, for it

00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:33,159
was as if the house itself had turned its eye upon us and dared us to follow.

00:14:33,159 --> 00:14:34,280
..

00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:39,039
Holmes's hand moved with surprising gentleness as he crouched, not to seize the cat, but

00:14:39,039 --> 00:14:43,399
to offer it his knuckles to scent as though they were old acquaintances rather than rivals

00:14:43,399 --> 00:14:44,080
in a crime.

00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:51,759
A creature does not trust a hurried hand. Watson and criminals are much the same,

00:14:51,759 --> 00:14:55,860
for both fear being snatched when they least expect it.

00:14:55,860 --> 00:15:01,120
The black cat sniffed him, whiskers twitching, and allowed Holmes to slip his fingers beneath

00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:04,700
the ribbon at its throat, drawing free the torn green velvet scrap.

00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:05,740
..

00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:12,539
This velvet is cut from the cabinet lining, and it is torn, not trimmed, which means the

00:15:12,539 --> 00:15:17,589
The animal caught it while the drawer was open and the jewel removed with speed.

00:15:17,589 --> 00:15:21,629
That cap belongs to the cook's boy, Mr. Holmes,

00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:24,670
and it has never been allowed in the study, not once,

00:15:24,670 --> 00:15:27,690
not in all the months that has prowled our kitchens.

00:15:27,690 --> 00:15:30,549
Oh, cats go where they please, madam.

00:15:30,549 --> 00:15:31,299
Yuck!

00:15:31,299 --> 00:15:37,639
But they do not learn to steal a jewel unless a human mind has first imagined the lesson.

00:15:37,639 --> 00:15:40,559
The maid, Elsie, hovered near the doorway,

00:15:40,559 --> 00:15:45,679
way, wringing her apron, a fear plain enough. Yet Holmes did not look at her with suspicion

00:15:45,679 --> 00:15:52,840
so much as with curiosity. Elsie, your shoes are damp with garden earth, and your sleeves carry

00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:58,450
the faintest trace of ash, which suggests you have been outside, near the glasshouse stove,

00:15:58,450 --> 00:16:05,879
within the past hour. I went to fetch herbs for the cook, sir, and the glasshouse is warm,

00:16:05,879 --> 00:16:14,390
and the ashes cling to everything and I swear again I did no wrong, though I know swearing is cheap.

00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:24,150
Cheap indeed, yet occasionally useful. Now tell me, did you ever see anyone feed this cat something finer than kitchen scraps?

00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:30,090
Something like cream served in a saucer, as if the animal were a guest?

00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:41,129
Miss Helena Shaw feeds it cream, sir, when she visits, and she laughs when it grubs against her skirts, and she says it has the cleverest eyes in London.

00:16:41,129 --> 00:16:47,379
Hones's head tilted slightly, and I recognised the motion as the click of an internal lock, one more tumbler falling into place.

00:16:47,379 --> 00:16:53,379
Miss Helena Shaw, the art dealer's sister, a visitor with leisure,

00:16:53,379 --> 00:17:00,370
wise, and leisure is often the disguise of mischief. Where is she now, Lady Winterbourne?

00:17:00,370 --> 00:17:06,819
In the drawing-room with the others, Mr. Holmes, though I cannot believe you mean to imply that

00:17:06,819 --> 00:17:11,079
Helena would stoop to theft, for she is gentle and reads poetry aloud.

00:17:11,079 --> 00:17:17,960
loud. Poetly is no shield against appetite, madam, and gentle voices often conceal sharp

00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:23,789
intentions. So let us hear what she has to say before we decide what she is.

00:17:23,789 --> 00:17:29,119
We returned to the drawing-room, where the air was thick with restrained outrage and the sugary

00:17:29,119 --> 00:17:34,200
scent of untouched tea. The guests sat like figures in a painting of discomfort, Sir Lionel

00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:39,420
red-faced and indignant, Colonel Rookwood stiff as a ramrod, Reverend Merriweather pale with moral

00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:44,680
and Mr. Stress, Percival Shaw, smoothing his moustache as if stroking his own nerves.

00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:45,720
..

00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:52,620
Good evening again, ladies and gentlemen, and I ask your pardon for interrupting your indignation.

00:17:52,620 --> 00:17:57,339
But it will keep, whereas evidence has a regrettable habit of vanishing.

00:17:57,339 --> 00:17:58,340
..

00:17:58,340 --> 00:18:02,680
This is outrageous, Holmes, absolutely outrageous to be detained here like pickpockets

00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:06,850
when we are people of standing and have done nothing but accept hospitality.

00:18:06,850 --> 00:18:12,059
Your standing is precisely what makes you dangerous, Sir Lionel,

00:18:12,059 --> 00:18:18,759
because standing provides cover, and criminals love nothing so much as cover.

00:18:18,759 --> 00:18:23,179
Sir Lionel sputtered, but Holmes turned smoothly to a slender young woman by the fireplace,

00:18:23,179 --> 00:18:27,199
whose hands lay folded in her lap with an air of practiced serenity.

00:18:27,199 --> 00:18:31,039
Hmm. Mr. Hmm. Mr. Hmm.

00:18:31,039 --> 00:18:32,119
Hmm.

00:18:32,119 --> 00:18:38,400
Holmes, if you have come to accuse me, pray do it quickly, for I find prolonged suspense

00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:43,059
far more distressing than a direct insult delivered with conviction.

00:18:43,059 --> 00:18:45,300
...

00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:49,509
Admire your clarity, Miss Shaw, and I will repay it with my own.

00:18:49,509 --> 00:18:56,259
You have been feeding a black cat in this house, and that cat has carried away a scrap

00:18:56,259 --> 00:18:59,220
of velvet torn from the jewel cabinet.

00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:08,960
cabinet. I have fed the cat, certainly, because it is a hungry creature. And it seems to me no

00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:14,940
sin to be kind to an animal merely because human beings are so often unkind to each other.

00:19:14,940 --> 00:19:16,960
...

00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:22,980
Kindness is admirable, yet training is another matter. And you have the hands of someone

00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:27,740
one accustomed to handling delicate objects, not merely sauces of cream.

00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:28,900
..

00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:32,980
Miss Shaw's eyes narrowed a fraction, and in that fraction I sensed a sharper mind

00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:38,869
than Lady Winterbourne wished to admit. You think my hands give me away, Mr. Peck, Holmes,

00:19:38,869 --> 00:19:45,819
but your own hands are stained with chemicals, and yet you do not confess to poisoning anyone

00:19:45,819 --> 00:19:53,079
one who displeases you. Touché, and since you have a taste for fencing, let us fence with facts.

00:19:53,079 --> 00:20:00,339
When did you last enter the study, and did you at any point remain there alone? I entered when

00:20:00,339 --> 00:20:05,759
your hostess showed us the prints, and I remained only long enough to admire the line work,

00:20:05,759 --> 00:20:12,779
and I was never alone. How? Unless you count the moment when the colonel stepped away to cough.

00:20:12,779 --> 00:20:17,799
I did cough, Holmes, because the study reeks of cigar smoke and varnish

00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:21,799
and I am not ashamed of lungs that object to fashionable pollution.

00:20:21,799 --> 00:20:25,960
A cough is not shameful, Colonel, but it can be convenient

00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:31,460
because it draws eyes and turns bodies away, which gives hands a moment of freedom.

00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:32,859
..

00:20:32,859 --> 00:20:36,220
The Colonel's jaw tightened and I saw the strain of a man unused

00:20:36,220 --> 00:20:39,420
to being treated as a variable in another's equation.

00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:41,440
Hmm, Mr. Hmm.

00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:51,539
Holmes, this manner of questioning is unseemly and I beg you to remember that we are not heathens in an alley but Christian souls gathered in friendship.

00:20:51,539 --> 00:20:57,840
Reverend, I respect your profession but I do not share your confidence in Christian souls.

00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:05,759
For I have seen too many of them cheat at cards and then pray for forgiveness as if prayer were a receipt.

00:21:05,759 --> 00:21:12,720
seat. At that, Mr. Percival Shaw gave a small, thin laugh and it struck me as oddly timed,

00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:23,009
like a man stepping on a stage cue. Mr. Shaw, you laugh as if this were entertainment. Yet,

00:21:23,009 --> 00:21:29,140
you are an art dealer and art dealers, in my experience, are always entertained by the price

00:21:29,140 --> 00:21:34,640
of things. Surely, Holmes, you cannot begrudge me a little humour to soften a tense evening.

00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:40,730
And besides, jewels are not my trade unless one counts the tasteful brooches worn by patrons.

00:21:40,730 --> 00:21:47,539
Your trade is desire, Mr. Shaw, and desire has many faces.

00:21:47,539 --> 00:21:54,440
Now, would you mind showing me your hands, palms and nails as if you were a schoolboy caught stealing jam?

00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,920
...

00:21:56,920 --> 00:22:01,079
Shaw hesitated, just a breath too long, before extending his hands.

00:22:01,079 --> 00:22:06,710
There is a faint green dust beneath your light thumbnail, Mr. Shaw,

00:22:06,710 --> 00:22:13,639
which suggests you have recently handled a stone that sheds microscopic flecks along its setting.

00:22:13,639 --> 00:22:18,440
That is absurd, Holmes, and you are making tricks with candlelight and imagination,

00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:22,840
because I have handled nothing but wine glasses and polite conversation.

00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:26,539
Imagination is Watson's weakness, not mine, Inspector.

00:22:26,539 --> 00:22:33,099
inspector. Bring your lamp closer. And Watson, if you would be so kind, hold Mr. Shaw's hand

00:22:33,099 --> 00:22:38,579
steady without drinking it. I complied, though I confessed the physical contact made me uneasy,

00:22:38,579 --> 00:22:43,200
for Shaw's skin was cold and slightly moist, like a man who had been running in secret.

00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:51,220
The dust is real, and now we shall ask how it arrived there. Did you, perhaps, attempt to open

00:22:51,220 --> 00:22:54,980
on the cabinet and catch your nail on the velvet as you withdrew.

00:22:54,980 --> 00:22:56,120
..

00:22:56,120 --> 00:23:01,740
You are turning a speck into a gallows, Holmes, and I will not stand for it, because I have

00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:05,880
done nothing except what any guest might do in a host's house.

00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:10,070
You have done one uncommon thing, mister.

00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:16,200
Sure, you have the faint scent of Balearian on your cuffs, and Balearian is used to entice

00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:19,940
cats, which explains how the animal came to be your accomplice.

00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:28,009
At the mention of Valerian, Lady Winterbourne pressed a hand to her throat and Miss Shaw's calm broke, if only by her hair.

00:23:28,009 --> 00:23:37,269
Valerian, you're same as the Valerian, Holmes, and you speak as if my brother was sprinkling cat attractant like sugar.

00:23:37,269 --> 00:23:42,960
Yet you forget that half the fashionable world keeps such tinctures to soothe nerves.

00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,460
..

00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:48,799
Precisely, Miss Shaw, and the other half keeps them to manipulate animals.

00:23:48,799 --> 00:23:52,549
And your brother's tincture is not on a lady's handkerchief,

00:23:52,549 --> 00:23:56,299
but rubbed into his cuffs where a cact would nuzzle.

00:23:56,299 --> 00:24:00,449
By God, Shaw, if you have brought us into a sordid business,

00:24:00,449 --> 00:24:01,730
you will answer to me,

00:24:01,730 --> 00:24:04,079
because I will not have my name splashed in mud

00:24:04,079 --> 00:24:06,320
by a man who sells paintings to gamblers.

00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:09,039
Hold your tongue, Grease, for you know nothing.

00:24:09,039 --> 00:24:11,650
And Holmes, if you are so clever, find the jewel,

00:24:11,650 --> 00:24:15,579
because accusing me does not conjure it back onto the velvet.

00:24:15,579 --> 00:24:18,079
You are correct, Mr.

00:24:18,079 --> 00:24:19,400
..

00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:28,299
Sure, accusation is merely noise without recovery, so let us follow the cat's path, for I suspect the jewel has already left this house.

00:24:28,299 --> 00:24:29,380
..

00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:36,130
Holmes crossed to the heart-rug, where a small smear of grey ash lay, and he knelt, drawing from it a tiny loop of fine thread.

00:24:36,130 --> 00:24:44,559
This is stage-thread, Watson, the sort used in theatres to raise a ghostly lantern, or move a prop without visible hand.

00:24:44,559 --> 00:24:50,990
and it is fresh, which means the theft was performed with theatrical contrivance.

00:24:50,990 --> 00:24:55,340
The anonymous letter's phrase returned to me, the cat's eye would blink for me,

00:24:55,340 --> 00:25:01,490
and I felt, with sudden certainty, that we had stepped into a drama written by someone who enjoyed applause.

00:25:01,490 --> 00:25:07,960
Lady Winterbourne, is there a theatre connection among your guests, or among your servants,

00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:11,880
or among those who have lately sought your patronage?

00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:17,480
Colonel Rookwood sits on a charity board that funds performances for veterans

00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:20,190
and Miss Shaw attends the opera.

00:25:20,190 --> 00:25:23,500
But beyond that, I know of nothing.

00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:28,030
Unless you count my husband's fondness for amateur dramatics.

00:25:28,030 --> 00:25:33,279
Amateur dramatics are often the training ground for professional deceit, Colonel.

00:25:33,279 --> 00:25:35,160
..

00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:40,500
Did your charity board recently engage any stagehands or illusionists

00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:42,940
who might have learned of this jewel?

00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:45,639
We engaged a man named Silas Morn.

00:25:45,639 --> 00:25:48,460
Holmes, a fellow with nimble fingers

00:25:48,460 --> 00:25:51,960
who claimed he could make coins vanish to delight the wounded.

00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:55,639
And I confess, I disliked him at once.

00:25:55,639 --> 00:25:58,849
Silas Morn, yes, I have heard of him.

00:25:58,849 --> 00:26:00,910
A conjurer turned burglar.

00:26:00,910 --> 00:26:02,369
And if he is involved,

00:26:02,369 --> 00:26:06,099
the jewel may already be headed for a fence near the river.

00:26:06,099 --> 00:26:08,119
Holmes rose with sudden decision,

00:26:08,119 --> 00:26:09,980
his lango shedding like a cloak,

00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:12,289
revealing the keen energy beneath.

00:26:12,289 --> 00:26:15,380
Inspector, you will keep these people here

00:26:15,380 --> 00:26:18,059
and prevent melodrama from becoming murder

00:26:18,059 --> 00:26:23,430
while Watson and I follow the only witness that does not lie, the cat.

00:26:23,430 --> 00:26:27,730
Follow a cat? Mr. Beanings, Mr. Chunks, Combs,

00:26:27,730 --> 00:26:29,440
and you expect me to take that seriously

00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:32,880
when I have constables and wardens and the Queen's authority behind me?

00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:35,019
You have authority, Inspector,

00:26:35,019 --> 00:26:38,539
but I have results, and results, I find,

00:26:38,539 --> 00:26:44,579
are more persuasive than uniforms so kindly do as you were told with that

00:26:44,579 --> 00:26:48,900
Holmes whistled softly and to my amazement the black cat whose which had

00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:53,539
slipped into the hallway trotted back as if summoned by a familiar signal there

00:26:53,539 --> 00:26:59,779
Watson you see it has been trained and now we shall discover by whom because

00:26:59,779 --> 00:27:05,740
training leaves trails as surely as footprints do we followed the creature

00:27:05,740 --> 00:27:11,299
out into the garden, where damp soil darkened the paths and the shrubs shivered under a chilly wind.

00:27:11,299 --> 00:27:16,960
The cat moved with purpose, not prowling, not hunting, but navigating, and it led us toward

00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:21,720
the glass house at the far end of the grounds. Observe the broken twig here, Watson, and the

00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:27,180
pressed grass there, for even in a garden, haste writes its story plainly.

00:27:27,180 --> 00:27:33,119
Inside the glass house, warmth struck our faces, and the air smelled of wet earth and exotic plants.

00:27:33,119 --> 00:27:38,240
cameras, and near the stove I saw a small wooden box half hidden beneath a bench.

00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:43,829
Do not touch it yet, Watson, because boxes often carry surprises,

00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:47,980
and surprises are better met with caution than courage.

00:27:47,980 --> 00:27:51,960
Holmes lifted the lid with his cane, and within lay not the cat's eye,

00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:57,059
but a folded playbill, damp and trumpled, bearing the name of a music hall on the strand.

00:27:57,059 --> 00:28:03,500
The strand, of course, where applause is bought and secrets are sold.

00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:10,079
And now the adventure leaves Kensington and enters the city's brighter, dirtier heart.

00:28:10,079 --> 00:28:11,139
..

00:28:11,139 --> 00:28:16,809
The cat rubbed against Holmes' leg and Holmes, without looking down, murmured as if to it directly,

00:28:16,809 --> 00:28:18,550
Biding go!

00:28:18,550 --> 00:28:24,210
You have done well, my nocturnal friend, but your master is impatient,

00:28:24,210 --> 00:28:28,839
and we shall pay him a visit before the curtain falls.

00:28:28,839 --> 00:28:33,980
As we hurried back toward the street, I felt the gaze gather speed like a carriage rolling downhill,

00:28:33,980 --> 00:28:39,860
and I knew, with that particular dread and exhilaration, that London's night would not be quiet for us.

00:28:39,860 --> 00:28:43,700
The handsome bore us toward the strand as twilight deepened,

00:28:43,700 --> 00:28:47,119
and the gas lamps flared into life like rows of watchful eyes,

00:28:47,119 --> 00:28:52,380
casting their jaundiced glow upon faces that hurry past in search of pleasure or escape.

00:28:52,380 --> 00:28:55,329
Hone sat opposite me, jint out, eyes distant.

00:28:55,329 --> 00:28:59,740
Yet I could tell by the set of his mouth that his mind raced through possibilities

00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:02,740
with the cold joy of a mathematician nearing proof.

00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:03,859
..

00:29:03,859 --> 00:29:09,750
A jewel theft with a trained cat and stage-thread Watson is not merely crime.

00:29:09,750 --> 00:29:15,740
It is performance, which means the culprit craves control and an audience.

00:29:15,740 --> 00:29:18,880
and we shall deny him both.

00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:21,789
I tried to summon my own deductive reasoning,

00:29:21,789 --> 00:29:23,700
recalling Holmes' constant instruction

00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:26,819
and I ventured with careful phrasing

00:29:26,819 --> 00:29:29,960
lest I offer him a sentence too short for your constraints

00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:32,019
and too foolish for his patience.

00:29:32,019 --> 00:29:35,110
If the thief is theatrical and known to Colonel Rookwood,

00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:39,140
then Silas Morn might have used the charity show as reconnaissance

00:29:39,140 --> 00:29:41,980
and Mr. Percival Shaw, being an art dealer,

00:29:41,980 --> 00:29:44,700
could serve as his respectable channel to sell the stone.

00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:52,220
A respectable channel, yes. And your thought is almost sound, Watson. Watson, except you still

00:29:52,220 --> 00:29:57,319
think in straight lines when criminals prefer circles. When—

00:29:57,319 --> 00:30:02,180
Holmes leaned forward as the cab slew near a music hall, whose painted façade shouted

00:30:02,180 --> 00:30:06,039
gaiety-wile as doorways swallowed men into shadow.

00:30:06,039 --> 00:30:12,559
The cat's eye is too famous to sell openly, so it must be altered or hidden,

00:30:12,559 --> 00:30:15,099
and alteration requires a jeweler

00:30:15,099 --> 00:30:17,039
while hiding requires a place

00:30:17,039 --> 00:30:18,900
where one may move unseen.

00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:19,940
..

00:30:19,940 --> 00:30:21,500
The music hall's entrance

00:30:21,500 --> 00:30:23,599
was a riot of posters and barkers

00:30:23,599 --> 00:30:24,859
and laughter spilled out

00:30:24,859 --> 00:30:25,859
mixed with cigarette smoke

00:30:25,859 --> 00:30:28,559
and the faint brassy wheeze of a cornet.

00:30:28,559 --> 00:30:30,140
Holmes paid the driver

00:30:30,140 --> 00:30:31,449
and drew me into the crowd.

00:30:31,449 --> 00:30:32,349
One died dear,

00:30:32,349 --> 00:30:33,920
his posture instantly changing

00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,039
from consulting detective

00:30:35,039 --> 00:30:36,359
to idle gentleman

00:30:36,359 --> 00:30:38,869
as if he put on disguises without costumes.

00:30:38,869 --> 00:30:41,240
We shall not enter by the front, Watson,

00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:44,440
because the front is for customers and policemen,

00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:48,759
and I prefer to be neither when I seek truth.

00:30:48,759 --> 00:30:51,860
He led me down a narrow alley beside the theatre,

00:30:51,860 --> 00:30:55,210
where refuse bins and damp brick conspired to sour the air,

00:30:55,210 --> 00:30:58,119
and there, hello, half hidden behind a rain-battle,

00:30:58,119 --> 00:31:00,050
a stage-door stood ajar.

00:31:00,050 --> 00:31:03,070
Observe the fresh chalk-mark on the lintel, Watson,

00:31:03,070 --> 00:31:05,549
a conjurer's sign to guide his fellows.

00:31:05,549 --> 00:31:08,599
Hey! And tell me what you deduce from that.

00:31:08,599 --> 00:31:18,059
I deduced that Silas Morn expects company and that this hall is not merely a place of entertainment but a meeting point for those who speak in codes and prefer not to be seen.

00:31:18,059 --> 00:31:31,900
Better, Watson, because you have moved from noticing to inferring. And that is the whole theory of deduction, from small truths to larger ones without the weak bridge of wishful thinking.

00:31:31,900 --> 00:31:39,409
We slipped inside, moving through dim corridors where ropes hung like vines and the floorboards cleaked with a tired protest.

00:31:39,409 --> 00:31:42,920
Who the devil are you prowling where you do not belong?

00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:49,279
Because the next man I find here, without a pass, will meet my boot and not my hospitality.

00:31:49,279 --> 00:31:53,040
....

00:31:53,040 --> 00:32:01,019
You are Mr. Hmm, blinched the stage manager, and you have ink on your left thumb and grease on your right cuff,

00:32:01,019 --> 00:32:04,740
which means you write schedules and move scenally,

00:32:04,740 --> 00:32:08,299
and therefore you are exactly the man I require.

00:32:08,299 --> 00:32:09,619
..

00:32:09,619 --> 00:32:13,250
That's a fine speech, sir, but it does not answer my question.

00:32:13,250 --> 00:32:17,889
And I have no time for cleverness when the curtain is due in ten minutes.

00:32:17,889 --> 00:32:21,750
Then you have even less time for crime.

00:32:21,750 --> 00:32:26,079
I am Sherlock Holmes, and I am looking for Silas Morn,

00:32:26,079 --> 00:32:31,119
because he has misplaced something that does not belong to him.

00:32:31,119 --> 00:32:32,259
..

00:32:32,259 --> 00:32:34,799
At Holmes' name, the man's bravado wavered

00:32:34,799 --> 00:32:36,809
for even among the backstage roughs,

00:32:36,809 --> 00:32:39,710
Holmes' reputation travelled like a whispered warning.

00:32:39,710 --> 00:32:43,809
I know of no Silas Mone, Mr. Holmes,

00:32:43,809 --> 00:32:45,719
and if you keep me from my duties,

00:32:45,719 --> 00:32:49,920
the audience will riot and you will have more trouble than a jewel is worth.

00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:51,240
..

00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:53,859
You know him because you just lied

00:32:53,859 --> 00:32:57,279
and your eyes flicked to the trap door at your feet,

00:32:57,279 --> 00:33:00,639
which means your trouble is already beneath you.

00:33:00,639 --> 00:33:04,119
Before Blinch could shout, Holmes' hand darted,

00:33:04,119 --> 00:33:06,000
pressing two fingers to the man's wrist

00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:07,700
in a grip that was not cruel yet,

00:33:07,700 --> 00:33:09,420
was utterly commanding.

00:33:09,420 --> 00:33:13,599
You will remain quiet, Mr. Blinch,

00:33:13,599 --> 00:33:14,950
because if you do not,

00:33:14,950 --> 00:33:17,799
I shall make your wrist remember me for a week

00:33:17,799 --> 00:33:20,819
and that would impede your precious schedules.

00:33:20,819 --> 00:33:22,190
All right, all right.

00:33:22,190 --> 00:33:23,339
Keep your temper, sir,

00:33:23,339 --> 00:33:24,779
and I'll not raise a sound

00:33:24,779 --> 00:33:26,409
but I'll tell you plain.

00:33:26,409 --> 00:33:27,519
There are men down there

00:33:27,519 --> 00:33:28,579
I do not wish to cross.

00:33:28,579 --> 00:33:30,200
..

00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:32,140
Men who prefer shadows

00:33:32,140 --> 00:33:34,539
which makes them excellent targets

00:33:34,539 --> 00:33:36,640
for a man who studies shadows

00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:39,319
as if they were letters in a book.

00:33:39,319 --> 00:33:40,400
..

00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:41,859
Holmes lifted the trapdoor

00:33:41,859 --> 00:33:43,490
and a stale breath rose from below.

00:33:43,490 --> 00:33:44,429
Heavy with sweat.

00:33:44,429 --> 00:33:45,019
Cheat gin.

00:33:45,019 --> 00:33:45,650
Jeep.

00:33:45,650 --> 00:33:47,039
And something medicinal

00:33:47,039 --> 00:33:48,299
that pricked the nostrils.

00:33:48,299 --> 00:33:50,440
A ladder descended into darkness

00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,960
and I felt that familiar

00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,160
tightening in my chest

00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:57,660
the soldier's instinct that says danger lies below and duty says descend.

00:33:57,660 --> 00:34:02,680
Keep close, Watson, and keep your revolver ready, though if you fire.

00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:05,279
Do try to hit the man you intend,

00:34:05,279 --> 00:34:08,739
because straped bullets are the clumsiest form of deduction.

00:34:08,739 --> 00:34:10,000
..

00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:13,280
We climbed down into a basement chamber lit by a single lantern

00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:15,320
where men sat at a table playing cards

00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:18,199
and a thin figure in a velvet waistcoat stood apart,

00:34:18,199 --> 00:34:21,090
polishing a coin as if it were his soul.

00:34:21,090 --> 00:34:27,420
Well now, the famous Mr. Mr. Holmes, come to applaud my little enterprises, and with

00:34:27,420 --> 00:34:30,599
a doctor too, as if you expect someone to bleed before the encore.

00:34:30,599 --> 00:34:32,340
..

00:34:32,340 --> 00:34:38,199
Silas Morn, you have the hands of a conjurer, and the conscience of a rat, and somewhere

00:34:38,199 --> 00:34:42,869
near you is a jewel that belongs to Lady Winterbourne.

00:34:42,869 --> 00:34:49,340
Lady Winterbourne, you say, and you speak her name with such confidence, as if highborn

00:34:49,340 --> 00:34:53,599
Women never lose things and low-born men never find them

00:34:53,599 --> 00:35:01,199
Morn's eyes glittered and I saw then the peculiar vanity Holmes had predicted the showman's delight in being recognized even as villain

00:35:01,199 --> 00:35:08,480
You did not find it Morn you stole it and you used a trained cat stage thread and valerian

00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:13,149
Which means you planned it with care and executed it with speed

00:35:13,149 --> 00:35:15,260
Planning is artistry

00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:17,960
Mr. Horns, an artist who deserves payment

00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:20,420
And if the world insists on worshipping stones

00:35:20,420 --> 00:35:23,869
Then the world should not complain when a priest takes an offering

00:35:23,869 --> 00:35:25,679
Spare me your philosophy

00:35:25,679 --> 00:35:29,239
Because it is merely greed in a borrowed coat

00:35:29,239 --> 00:35:31,180
Where is the cat's eye?

00:35:31,180 --> 00:35:35,460
Aye, and do not waste my patience with theatrics

00:35:35,460 --> 00:35:38,039
The cat's eye has blinked for me, Horns

00:35:38,039 --> 00:35:39,940
And it will blink again for another buyer

00:35:39,940 --> 00:35:42,099
And by the time you return to Kensington

00:35:42,099 --> 00:35:45,880
you'll find nothing but an empty niche and a bruised bride.

00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:50,659
Hones' gaze swept the basement, counting exits, weapons and men

00:35:50,659 --> 00:35:52,820
and I saw his mind choose a route to danger

00:35:52,820 --> 00:35:56,289
with the same calm precision he used to choose a chemical solution.

00:35:56,289 --> 00:36:01,800
There is a side door behind you with damp hinges, suggesting recent use.

00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:07,699
And your boots carry river mud, suggesting you have been to a wharf within the hour.

00:36:07,699 --> 00:36:11,280
You talk too much, Hones, and talk makes men thirsty.

00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:15,579
So perhaps I'll have my lads pour you a drink you won't enjoy.

00:36:15,579 --> 00:36:20,640
Your lads are nervous because they are criminals, not soldiers.

00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:25,889
And they will scatter if they believe the police are above, which they are.

00:36:25,889 --> 00:36:31,239
Because I left a message for Inspector Lestrade on my way here.

00:36:31,239 --> 00:36:32,340
..

00:36:32,340 --> 00:36:38,159
That last statement was delivered with such serene certainty that even I nearly believed it,

00:36:38,159 --> 00:36:40,340
though I had seen no such message delivered.

00:36:40,340 --> 00:36:40,940
Oh!

00:36:40,940 --> 00:36:42,300
..

00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:48,199
Watson, at the count of three, overturn the lantern, because darkness is the one costume

00:36:48,199 --> 00:36:50,710
in which you might outshine me.

00:36:50,710 --> 00:36:55,029
I understood at once, and though my heart hammered, I forced my hand steady.

00:36:55,029 --> 00:36:58,069
Mormon steadiness is the only prayer worth seeing.

00:36:58,069 --> 00:37:05,690
One, two, three, and now, gentlemen, let us see whether you can fight without an audience.

00:37:05,690 --> 00:37:14,130
I lunged and struck the lantern and it toppled, oil flaring briefly before the flame died, plunging the room into chaos and curses.

00:37:14,130 --> 00:37:19,300
In the dark, bodies collided, chairs scraped and a fist grazed my cheek.

00:37:19,300 --> 00:37:23,090
But I kept low and moved toward the sound of Morn's voice.

00:37:23,090 --> 00:37:28,679
You'll regret that, Doctor, because I always hated men who meddle in tricks they do not understand.

00:37:28,679 --> 00:37:36,639
You misunderstand, Morn, because this is no trick. It is deduction in motion.

00:37:36,639 --> 00:37:41,219
And you have just placed yourself exactly where I wanted you.

00:37:41,219 --> 00:37:47,220
There was a sharp thud, the unmistakable sound of Holmes' cane meeting bone. And then Morn hissed in pain.

00:37:47,220 --> 00:37:56,970
Your pocket, Morn, is heavier on the left. And that heaviness is not coins, because coins jingle. And yours do not.

00:37:56,970 --> 00:38:01,079
Curse you, Holmes. You're like a devil in the dark. And I swear I'll...

00:38:01,079 --> 00:38:05,510
I caught Morn's arm, and between my grip and Holmes' relentless pressure,

00:38:05,510 --> 00:38:10,500
we forced him against the wall. Watson, strike a match, and let us

00:38:10,500 --> 00:38:14,369
see what our performer has concealed behind his velvet.

00:38:14,369 --> 00:38:19,739
My trembling fingers found a matchbox, and I sparked a flame. The small light revealed

00:38:19,739 --> 00:38:23,880
Morn's face twisted with fury, and Holmes' hand already within the man's coat.

00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:30,849
Here it is not, which means it is elsewhere, which means you have passed it on already,

00:38:30,849 --> 00:38:35,470
and now your cleverness has become your noose.

00:38:35,470 --> 00:38:40,500
I pass nothing on, Holmes, because I do not trust buyers until I have their money,

00:38:40,500 --> 00:38:43,659
and I do not trust money until I can smell it.

00:38:43,659 --> 00:38:49,260
Then you have hidden it nearby, perhaps in a frock chest, perhaps in a costume,

00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:57,880
you, perhaps even on the cat itself, which you use as courier because no one suspects an animal.

00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:59,100
..

00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:02,750
At the mention of the cat, Morn's eyes flicked upward, and Hone saw it too,

00:39:02,750 --> 00:39:06,930
and without another word, he sprang toward a staircase leading to the stage above.

00:39:06,930 --> 00:39:11,260
Up, Watson, because the jewel is about to cross the footlights,

00:39:11,260 --> 00:39:16,619
and I refuse to let a thief take a ball with Lady Winterbourne's property.

00:39:16,619 --> 00:39:22,539
We burst onto the side of the stage as music swelled and the audience laughed at a clown's

00:39:22,539 --> 00:39:28,220
brad fall, unaware that a far more dangerous performance had just begun behind the curtain.

00:39:28,220 --> 00:39:32,920
The stage lights dazzled after the basement dark and the painted scenery bright cottages

00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:37,519
and absurdly blue skies seemed almost insulting in its cheerfulness.

00:39:37,519 --> 00:39:42,840
Homes moved like a shadow along the wings, avoiding the actors who pranced and sang while

00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:45,519
stagehands hauled ropes overhead with indifferent strength.

00:39:45,519 --> 00:39:50,989
friend. Look for the cat, Watson, because a courier must appear before the delivery,

00:39:50,989 --> 00:39:58,579
and this delivery, whole, I suspect, is meant to happen in full view, without being seen.

00:39:58,579 --> 00:40:04,760
My eyes scanned the clutter of props, trunks, hoops, false swords, false swords, and a glittering

00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:10,099
cabinet used in some illusion, and then I saw it, the black cat pursed atop a trunk near a man in

00:40:10,099 --> 00:40:11,340
a red waistcoat.

00:40:11,340 --> 00:40:14,199
That man is no stagehand Watson

00:40:14,199 --> 00:40:15,960
because he wears kid gloves

00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:16,880
under his costume.

00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,140
..

00:40:18,140 --> 00:40:20,219
And only someone handling

00:40:20,219 --> 00:40:21,860
valuables wears gloves

00:40:21,860 --> 00:40:24,150
where no audience can see them.

00:40:24,150 --> 00:40:25,980
The man's profile turned

00:40:25,980 --> 00:40:27,960
dew and I recognized with a

00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:29,739
jolt the sharp nose and

00:40:29,739 --> 00:40:32,250
neatly trimmed moustache of Mr. Percival Shaw.

00:40:32,250 --> 00:40:34,059
He stood there as if

00:40:34,059 --> 00:40:35,920
he belonged, offering a coin to the

00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:37,960
cat and the cat, obedient as

00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:39,880
any trained performer, leaned forward its

00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:47,159
scholar dwindling there is your circle watson not a line mons steals shock legitimizes and the

00:40:47,159 --> 00:40:54,559
theater provides cover applause and a dozen exits home stepped out not rushing but walking as though

00:40:54,559 --> 00:40:59,300
he had every right to be on that stage which in a sense he did for he was about to end the act

00:40:59,300 --> 00:41:00,320
..

00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:08,699
mr hmm sure you are admirably versatile selling art by day and fencing jewels by night yet i fear

00:41:08,699 --> 00:41:11,900
your newest acquisition will not remain in your catalogue.

00:41:11,900 --> 00:41:14,760
...

00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:20,590
Holmes, you meddling insect! You have no authority here and if you cause a scene,

00:41:20,590 --> 00:41:25,579
the crowd will tear this place apart before you find your precious stone.

00:41:25,579 --> 00:41:31,639
The crowd will see only what the spotlight tells them, sure, and the spotlight is not

00:41:31,639 --> 00:41:37,800
presently on us, which makes this the safest place in London, for quiet truth.

00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:38,840
..

00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:43,360
Shaw's hand darted toward the trunk and I saw the daint of something metallic, perhaps

00:41:43,360 --> 00:41:45,760
a small pistol suited for close quarters.

00:41:45,760 --> 00:41:50,619
Instinct and service took me and I stepped between him and Holmes, my voice firm though

00:41:50,619 --> 00:41:52,579
my pulse roared in my ears.

00:41:52,579 --> 00:41:57,420
Hmm, Mister, hmm, Shaw, you will put that weapon away because I have faced rifles in

00:41:57,420 --> 00:42:00,960
Afghanistan and I will not be threatened by a toy hidden among costumes?

00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:04,600
A brave speech, Doctor, and quite wasted.

00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:07,159
Because bravery does not stop lead.

00:42:07,159 --> 00:42:11,190
And lead is very democratic. In home it kills.

00:42:11,190 --> 00:42:18,109
Democracy is charming, Shaw, but your hand shakes, which means you have not killed before,

00:42:18,109 --> 00:42:23,220
which means you will hesitate, which means you will lose.

00:42:23,220 --> 00:42:27,820
Holmes's cane snapped upward, striking Shaw's wrist with surgical precision

00:42:27,820 --> 00:42:31,940
and the pistol clattered into a prop bucket with a hollow, comic sound.

00:42:31,940 --> 00:42:35,440
The cat leapt, startled, and as it did,

00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:40,890
something small in green flashed at its collar, caught in a tiny sewn pouch.

00:42:40,890 --> 00:42:46,029
Watson, the pouch, because the jewel rides the cat like a crown,

00:42:46,029 --> 00:42:50,960
and we must take it gently unless you prefer to be clawed into humility.

00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:52,039
..

00:42:52,039 --> 00:42:54,710
I moved slowly, murmuring nonsense soothingly,

00:42:54,710 --> 00:42:58,100
and the cat, perhaps recognizing Holmes' earlier kindness,

00:42:58,100 --> 00:43:01,600
allowed me to grasp the pouch and unfasten it.

00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:04,670
So the cat's eye slid into my palm, cold and heavy.

00:43:04,670 --> 00:43:09,210
And even in that backstage half-light, it seemed to shimmer with an inner pulse,

00:43:09,210 --> 00:43:11,890
as if alive to the drama of its own recovery.

00:43:11,890 --> 00:43:13,439
And I meant to use a projector.

00:43:13,439 --> 00:43:18,180
Elementary, as I warned you from the beginning, because criminals may be clever,

00:43:18,180 --> 00:43:20,099
but they are rarely original.

00:43:20,099 --> 00:43:24,500
And originality is the one quality I never underestimate.

00:43:24,500 --> 00:43:26,519
You have it then.

00:43:26,519 --> 00:43:28,119
And you think you have won.

00:43:28,119 --> 00:43:29,630
But you forget, Holmes.

00:43:29,630 --> 00:43:30,320
Holmes.

00:43:30,320 --> 00:43:34,619
The people like Lady Winterbourne are not ruined only by theft.

00:43:34,619 --> 00:43:36,480
They are ruined by stories.

00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:37,720
..

00:43:37,720 --> 00:43:40,319
Stories are Watson's province, Shaw.

00:43:40,319 --> 00:43:42,720
And he is kinder than I.

00:43:42,720 --> 00:43:44,010
But I am practical.

00:43:44,010 --> 00:43:48,510
And I shall prevent your story from breaching her doorstep.

00:43:48,510 --> 00:43:52,529
Shaw laughed bitterly, his bravado collapsing into spite.

00:43:52,529 --> 00:43:55,119
And behind us I heard the muffled roar of the audience

00:43:55,119 --> 00:43:57,939
as the onstage performance reached some comedic climax.

00:43:57,939 --> 00:44:00,210
You cannot stop gossip, Holmes.

00:44:00,210 --> 00:44:05,489
because gossip is London's true religion and it will kneel at any scandal offered to it.

00:44:05,489 --> 00:44:11,720
Perhaps, but I can redirect it, which is a form of control even pleases Henry.

00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:16,139
Now, Shaw, you will come with us quietly

00:44:16,139 --> 00:44:23,600
and you sign a confession that places all blame upon yourself and mourn.

00:44:23,600 --> 00:44:28,139
Confession, you say, as if I would destroy myself to spare a lady's pride

00:44:28,139 --> 00:44:31,579
when her pride is built on the backs of men like me.

00:44:31,579 --> 00:44:35,010
You will confess because the alternative is worse.

00:44:35,010 --> 00:44:39,189
I shall reveal not merely this theft,

00:44:39,189 --> 00:44:45,059
but the dozen smaller crimes by which you have fed your respectability,

00:44:45,059 --> 00:44:51,190
including the forged provenance you sold to Sir Lionel last year.

00:44:51,190 --> 00:44:55,280
Sir Lionel's name, spoken there, landed like a drop plate,

00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:56,980
and Shaw's face drained of colour

00:44:56,980 --> 00:44:59,760
for blackmail is most potent when it is true.

00:44:59,760 --> 00:45:01,960
You have no proof of that, Horns

00:45:01,960 --> 00:45:03,510
and even if you did,

00:45:03,510 --> 00:45:06,890
Greaves would deny it until his dying breath.

00:45:06,890 --> 00:45:09,320
Proof is a flexible thing, Shaw

00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:11,139
but fear is reliable

00:45:11,139 --> 00:45:12,880
and you are afraid

00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:16,740
which means you will do as I say.

00:45:16,740 --> 00:45:18,699
Shaw's shoulders sagged

00:45:18,699 --> 00:45:19,800
and in that moment,

00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:21,880
he looked less villain than weary man

00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:24,000
caught by the consequences of his own hunger.

00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:30,639
Watson, take the jewel and step back, because I will not have it damaged if this man decides

00:45:30,639 --> 00:45:33,380
to salvage dignity with violence.

00:45:33,380 --> 00:45:38,119
I tugged the cat's eye securely into my inner pocket, feeling its weight like responsibility

00:45:38,119 --> 00:45:43,219
itself and I watched Holmes guide Shaw toward the stage door with a hand that was firm yet

00:45:43,219 --> 00:45:44,909
oddly devoid of cruelty.

00:45:44,909 --> 00:45:50,139
You see, Watson, the goal is not to punish for sport but to restore order.

00:45:50,139 --> 00:45:54,059
And order is merely truth put back where it belongs.

00:45:54,059 --> 00:45:59,029
We delivered Shaw to a waiting constable whom Holmes summoned with a sharp whistle and a few murmur.

00:45:59,029 --> 00:45:59,769
The instructions.

00:45:59,769 --> 00:46:04,529
The ease of it suggesting that Holmes had indeed laid preparations beyond my knowledge.

00:46:04,529 --> 00:46:08,569
Yet, even as Shaw was taken away, a new complication arrived.

00:46:08,569 --> 00:46:11,670
Though, as all true adventures insist upon providing.

00:46:11,670 --> 00:46:13,650
Hmm, bravo, mister.

00:46:13,650 --> 00:46:16,239
Hmm, Holmes, a splendid finale.

00:46:16,239 --> 00:46:23,029
But you have forgotten that every showman keeps a last trick and mine is to vanish before the applause fades

00:46:23,029 --> 00:46:28,260
Mon appeared at the alimouth his face bruised his smile intact and in his hand

00:46:28,260 --> 00:46:33,019
He held a small glass vial that got the lamplight like liquid menace

00:46:33,019 --> 00:46:36,670
Do not be melodramatic Mon Mon

00:46:36,670 --> 00:46:44,019
Because poison is a vulgar shortcut taken by men who lack imagination and you by your own account

00:46:44,019 --> 00:46:45,219
worship imagination

00:46:45,219 --> 00:46:47,019
..

00:46:47,019 --> 00:46:54,550
Imagination, Holmes, is knowing that you and your doctor will hesitate to chase a man who might spill death in a crowded street.

00:46:54,550 --> 00:47:04,949
The alley behind him opened onto the strand's throng, and I realized with sudden alarm that one thrown vial could cause panic, injury, and perhaps worse, and Mon knew it.

00:47:04,949 --> 00:47:09,800
Watson, your choice is simple. Protect the crowd or catch the criminal.

00:47:09,800 --> 00:47:11,670
and since you are a doctor,

00:47:11,670 --> 00:47:13,980
you will choose the crowd,

00:47:13,980 --> 00:47:16,539
which is why Morn thinks he can escape.

00:47:16,539 --> 00:47:17,619
..

00:47:17,619 --> 00:47:18,850
Holmes' voice was calm,

00:47:18,850 --> 00:47:20,719
but I heard in it the hard edge of calculation

00:47:20,719 --> 00:47:23,360
and I understood that he was already planning

00:47:23,360 --> 00:47:25,159
to defeat Morn's last trick

00:47:25,159 --> 00:47:27,170
without sacrificing innocence.

00:47:27,170 --> 00:47:29,800
Morn, you will not throw that vial

00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:30,829
because if you do,

00:47:30,829 --> 00:47:32,170
I shall shout,

00:47:32,170 --> 00:47:32,949
fire,

00:47:32,949 --> 00:47:35,119
and the stampede will crush more

00:47:35,119 --> 00:47:36,519
than your poison ever could

00:47:36,519 --> 00:47:39,590
and that blood will be on your conscience.

00:47:39,590 --> 00:47:42,039
if you possess such a thing.

00:47:42,039 --> 00:47:44,220
You are a core man, Horns,

00:47:44,220 --> 00:47:46,260
and core men make dangerous bargains.

00:47:46,260 --> 00:47:47,880
But perhaps you are right

00:47:47,880 --> 00:47:50,150
that I dislike messy endings.

00:47:50,150 --> 00:47:52,680
For a heartbeat that few of us held still,

00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:54,119
like figures in a tableau,

00:47:54,119 --> 00:47:55,189
the vile poised,

00:47:55,189 --> 00:47:56,230
the jewel safe,

00:47:56,230 --> 00:47:57,640
the city indifferent.

00:47:57,640 --> 00:47:59,440
Put it down, Morn,

00:47:59,440 --> 00:48:01,569
and I will let you keep one thing,

00:48:01,569 --> 00:48:04,760
your illusion that you almost won.

00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:06,810
Almost won, you say,

00:48:06,810 --> 00:48:09,480
and that almost is the cruelest word

00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:16,039
in any language. But very well, Mr. Fondo teach. Horns, I will not poison strangers for the sake

00:48:16,039 --> 00:48:21,010
of my pride. Morn's fingers loosened, the vile luring, and in that fraction of surrender,

00:48:21,010 --> 00:48:25,430
Holmes moved fast as a striking snake, his cane hooking Morn's wrist. The vile flew,

00:48:25,430 --> 00:48:29,460
not into the street, but into a puddle where it shattered with a harmless hiss.

00:48:29,460 --> 00:48:33,260
Tan and Morn, off balance, stumbled forward into my grass.

00:48:33,260 --> 00:48:38,320
There, Watson, you see how deduction becomes action, and dissipate the choice,

00:48:38,320 --> 00:48:44,579
shape the outcome and the villains last trick becomes merely another line in the

00:48:44,579 --> 00:48:48,360
script as we held mourn for the constable I felt the night's tension

00:48:48,360 --> 00:48:52,719
begin to ebb yet I knew we still must return to winter-born house and stitch

00:48:52,719 --> 00:48:57,800
together not only the jewel but the torn fabric of reputation the journey back to

00:48:57,800 --> 00:49:02,739
Kensington felt longer than it had any right to as if London itself wished to

00:49:02,739 --> 00:49:07,340
delay the moment when truth reentered polite society home sat opposite me

00:49:07,340 --> 00:49:10,699
composed while I could not help fingering the jewel through my coat,

00:49:10,699 --> 00:49:14,380
feeling its hard certainty like a heartbeat that was not my own.

00:49:14,380 --> 00:49:20,060
You're thinking, Watson, that the case is finished because the jewel is recovered.

00:49:20,060 --> 00:49:27,539
But in truth, the harder work begins now because society fears scandal more than theft.

00:49:27,539 --> 00:49:30,739
I admitted as much and I chose my words carefully,

00:49:30,739 --> 00:49:35,179
determined that even my agreement would not be brief enough to offend the strict form you require.

00:49:35,179 --> 00:49:35,680
Why?

00:49:35,680 --> 00:49:38,930
I am thinking that returning the cat's eye is only half the cure.

00:49:38,930 --> 00:49:42,320
Holmes, because Lady Winterbourne's household has been pierced

00:49:42,320 --> 00:49:46,579
and her guests will carry whispers like contagion into every drawing room.

00:49:46,579 --> 00:49:47,820
..

00:49:47,820 --> 00:49:48,609
Precisely.

00:49:48,609 --> 00:49:54,820
And so we shall prescribe a remedy suited to that illness.

00:49:54,820 --> 00:49:57,659
A story cleaner than the truth,

00:49:57,659 --> 00:50:02,800
yet close enough to it that no one can contradict it without implicating themselves.

00:50:02,800 --> 00:50:07,619
themselves. Winterbourne House received us again in turmoil, though now the air tasted different,

00:50:07,619 --> 00:50:12,659
less like panic and more like exhausted dread. Inspector and constable stood about with that

00:50:12,659 --> 00:50:17,760
efficient stiffness which suggests authority, even when authority has been outpaced, and the

00:50:17,760 --> 00:50:24,780
Inspector, you may congratulate yourself, because by the time morning comes you will have a lested

00:50:24,780 --> 00:50:31,880
Silas Morn, known rogue, and Percival Shaw, known swindler, and the public will applaud

00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:32,619
your diligence.

00:50:32,619 --> 00:50:34,199
..

00:50:34,199 --> 00:50:35,489
If I applaud anything,

00:50:35,489 --> 00:50:37,800
Mr. Holmes, it is that. You brought

00:50:37,800 --> 00:50:39,719
the jewel back, though I still maintain you

00:50:39,719 --> 00:50:41,679
code Danger like it's a sweetheart and not a grave.

00:50:41,679 --> 00:50:42,699
..

00:50:42,699 --> 00:50:43,739
Danger and

00:50:43,739 --> 00:50:45,739
I have an understanding, Inspector.

00:50:45,739 --> 00:50:47,639
And now I require

00:50:47,639 --> 00:50:49,780
a private word with Lady

00:50:49,780 --> 00:50:51,340
Winterbourne and her husband

00:50:51,340 --> 00:50:53,699
because reputations are more

00:50:53,699 --> 00:50:56,360
fragile than glass vials.

00:50:56,360 --> 00:50:57,920
We were ushered

00:50:57,920 --> 00:50:59,699
into the study where Lord Winterbourne,

00:50:59,699 --> 00:51:01,769
a broad-shouldered man with tired eyes,

00:51:01,769 --> 00:51:04,489
stood by the cabinet as if guarding it with his body.

00:51:04,489 --> 00:51:06,349
Hmm, mister, hmm.

00:51:06,349 --> 00:51:09,159
Holmes, my wife tells me you have pursued this matter,

00:51:09,159 --> 00:51:11,949
and I confess I find the whole thing intolerable,

00:51:11,949 --> 00:51:15,300
because I cannot have thieves making a stage of my home.

00:51:15,300 --> 00:51:17,059
Nor can I, my lord,

00:51:17,059 --> 00:51:20,590
which is why I prefer to end the performance decisively.

00:51:20,590 --> 00:51:25,470
Watson, if you please, return the cat's eye to its velvet bed.

00:51:25,470 --> 00:51:29,569
I produced the jewel, and Lady Winterbourne gasped softly,

00:51:29,569 --> 00:51:31,760
her composure tracking at last.

00:51:31,760 --> 00:51:35,010
and I saw tears gather, though she tried to master them.

00:51:35,010 --> 00:51:40,829
It is truly back, and you do not know what weight you have lifted, mister.

00:51:40,829 --> 00:51:46,420
Holmes, because this stone was not merely property, it was trust given to me.

00:51:46,420 --> 00:51:53,210
Trust is best placed in people, madam, not in cabinets, but I take your meaning,

00:51:53,210 --> 00:52:00,179
and now we shall discuss how to keep your house from being blamed for what was, in truth,

00:52:00,179 --> 00:52:02,159
Truth and external conspiracy.

00:52:02,159 --> 00:52:03,199
..

00:52:03,199 --> 00:52:06,369
External conspiracy, you say, and I would like to believe it.

00:52:06,369 --> 00:52:08,789
Holmes, because if the theft came from within,

00:52:08,789 --> 00:52:10,619
if my servants or my guests,

00:52:10,619 --> 00:52:13,539
then I do not know how I should ever host a fend again.

00:52:13,539 --> 00:52:16,920
The theft was orchestrated by Silas Morn,

00:52:16,920 --> 00:52:18,960
aided by Percival Shaw,

00:52:18,960 --> 00:52:22,559
and facilitated by your guests only in the sense that

00:52:22,559 --> 00:52:26,430
polite gatherings provide cover and predictable movement.

00:52:26,430 --> 00:52:28,719
Your maid is innocent of intent,

00:52:28,719 --> 00:52:34,260
though she is guilty of believing too readily in the virtue of fashionable visitors,

00:52:34,260 --> 00:52:39,109
which is a common mistake among honest people.

00:52:39,109 --> 00:52:44,000
Thank you, sir, and I will remember that lesson as long as I live,

00:52:44,000 --> 00:52:49,140
because Friar has carved it into me deeper than any sermon could.

00:52:49,140 --> 00:52:53,119
Holmes turned then to Lord Winterbourne and his tone softened,

00:52:53,119 --> 00:52:57,440
not into sentiment or code, into something like pragmatic respect.

00:52:57,440 --> 00:53:04,360
My lord, the public explanation will be as follows. You received an anonymous threat.

00:53:04,360 --> 00:53:11,860
You informed Scotland Yard, quietly, and an attempted theft was foiled through vigilance

00:53:11,860 --> 00:53:18,500
and police action. The truth includes your guests and a trained cat and a theatre,

00:53:18,500 --> 00:53:24,710
but the public does not need that embroidery and your family's name will be spared.

00:53:24,710 --> 00:53:26,059
Needless spectacle.

00:53:26,059 --> 00:53:31,809
spectacle. And what of Sir Lionel Holmes, because he's already furious, and fury, in my experience,

00:53:31,809 --> 00:53:38,139
leaks into conversation, no matter how one tries to cock it. Sir Lionel will remain quiet,

00:53:38,139 --> 00:53:45,860
because his purchase of forged provenance from Shaw is a secret. He, he, what, afford to see

00:53:45,860 --> 00:53:51,500
daylight, and I shall remind him of that fact, with a letter written in very polite ink.

00:53:51,500 --> 00:53:55,829
Lady Winterbourne stared at Holmes as if seeing him anew, not merely as detective,

00:53:55,829 --> 00:53:57,699
But as strategist of the social battlefield,

00:53:57,699 --> 00:54:02,000
you would manipulate society's lies to preserve society's peace.

00:54:02,000 --> 00:54:07,039
Mr. Holmes, and I cannot decide whether that is admirable or frightening.

00:54:07,039 --> 00:54:09,019
It is neither, madam.

00:54:09,019 --> 00:54:13,769
It is necessary, because civilization is a thin coat of varnish,

00:54:13,769 --> 00:54:18,500
and London would rather polish varnish than repair the wood beneath.

00:54:18,500 --> 00:54:23,139
Lord Winterbourne exhaled, the sound of a man releasing the worst of his dread,

00:54:23,139 --> 00:54:25,779
and he offered Holmes his hand with awkward sincerity.

00:54:25,779 --> 00:54:42,139
then i am in your debt mr holmes and while i dislike owing debts i dislike disgrace more so name your fee and be done my fee is simple improve the cabinet mechanism dismiss any notion that wealth is protection

00:54:42,139 --> 00:54:48,179
And if you must keep jewels, keep also the humility to know they attract wolves.

00:54:48,179 --> 00:54:57,859
That, I confess, struck me as unusually modern for Holmes, and used, and I saw Lady Winterbone look at him with something like gratitude that did not require words.

00:54:57,859 --> 00:55:07,949
When we returned to Baker Street later, the city's noise fell distant, muffled by fatigue, and Mrs. Hudson's lamp in the sitting room shone like a promise of ordinary life resumed.

00:55:07,949 --> 00:55:16,309
Sit, Watson, and tell me what you learned, for if you cannot articulate it, then you have not truly observed it.

00:55:16,309 --> 00:55:23,929
I sat, and though I was tired, I forced my mind to retrace the case, Hayes, to turn it into lessons rather than mere excitement.

00:55:23,929 --> 00:55:30,769
I learned that the smallest details like Valerian on a cuff or stage thread in ash can outweigh the loud declarations of innocence,

00:55:30,769 --> 00:55:34,800
and that criminals often rely on the blindness of respectable people.

00:55:34,800 --> 00:55:41,279
Good. And what else, Watson? Because you are still circling the point without landing upon it.

00:55:41,279 --> 00:55:51,719
I learned that rhyme is not always brute force, but sometimes theater, and that the thief who loves performance will build a scheme that is clever only because it assumes no one will look behind the curtain or...

00:55:51,719 --> 00:56:06,280
better watson and now the final step you learned that deduction is not a parlor game but the discipline of refusing comforting explanations until the uncomfortable truth is proven

00:56:06,280 --> 00:56:08,340
...

00:56:08,340 --> 00:56:11,289
Combs rose then, and without another word, took up his violin,

00:56:11,289 --> 00:56:15,779
drawing from it a slow, surging melody that seemed to echo the cat's eyes shifting light.

00:56:15,779 --> 00:56:20,440
Hmm, as he played, hmm, I watched the fires glow flicker on the mantle

00:56:20,440 --> 00:56:24,149
and thought of that green jewel resting again in its velvet niche,

00:56:24,149 --> 00:56:25,739
as if nothing had happened.

00:56:25,739 --> 00:56:29,029
Yet something had happened, for London had revealed, once more,

00:56:29,029 --> 00:56:32,210
its dual nature, bright facades masking basements,

00:56:32,210 --> 00:56:35,559
laughter drowning danger, and polite hands capable of theft,

00:56:35,559 --> 00:56:37,980
left, when temptation is dressed as art.

00:56:37,980 --> 00:56:44,239
Watson, you were right this one down, and you will call it The Adventure of the Cat's

00:56:44,239 --> 00:56:48,320
Eye, but do try to resist making me sound like a romantic hero.

00:56:48,320 --> 00:56:49,799
..

00:56:49,799 --> 00:56:54,679
I smiled despite myself, because even after all our adventures, Holmes still feared sentiment

00:56:54,679 --> 00:56:59,309
as if it were an infection, and perhaps that was why his clarity remained so sharp.

00:56:59,309 --> 00:57:03,940
I answered him with the honest affection of a friend who knows he will be ignored and

00:57:03,940 --> 00:57:06,010
and yet speaks any way.

00:57:06,010 --> 00:57:08,820
Careful again that my line should not be short,

00:57:08,820 --> 00:57:11,039
for you demanded length and life together.

00:57:11,039 --> 00:57:13,989
My dear Holmes, if I make you sound heroic,

00:57:13,989 --> 00:57:18,119
it will be because the truth of your mind is heroic in its own strange way,

00:57:18,119 --> 00:57:21,349
and if that troubles you, then you should have been less brilliant.

00:57:21,349 --> 00:57:24,420
Then I shall endeavour to be dull tomorrow, Watson,

00:57:24,420 --> 00:57:27,949
though I warn you, dullness does not suit me,

00:57:27,949 --> 00:57:32,019
and London has a habit of refusing to let me rest.

00:57:32,019 --> 00:57:38,940
The violin's note rose, the fire crackled, and outside, the city rolled on, indifferent and hungry,

00:57:38,940 --> 00:57:42,539
as if already preparing its next mystery, to lay at our doorstep.

00:57:42,539 --> 00:57:42,800
.

